adrFormatAddress: 153 3rd Ave, New York, NY 10003, USA

editorialSummary.text: Casual counter-serve chain for build-your-own sandwiches & salads, with health-conscious options.

originalText.text:
I had been here before and once I went when it was 20 minutes before closing and the doors were locked and the lights out. Then another time, I came 50 minutes after opening and the door was locked and the employee had to come to the door and unlock it for me.

It was clear she had a bad attitude already and didn't hear my orders. Then she just threw all of the vegetables in a very careless fashion and basically gave me a mess of a sandwich. The ingredients also looked very badly maintained. If you want to try your luck and health here, go for it. I would not recommend it.

Don't trust the positive reviews. They seem to be friends or paid. It's honestly not a great place and if you wanted better Subway, there's a much friendlier, cleaner Subway two blocks west near Union Square. It's located next to Bravo Pizza.

originalText.text: No. Don't even think about it. There's a reason Subway restaurants are all over the globe: some of them are clean and welcoming, and the staff make you tasty, fresh sandwiches with a smile. THAT IS NOT THIS PLACE. Odds are before your server has put a skimpy slice of pre-portioned green chicken on your bread you'll be wondering if he'd chase you if you made a run for it. Don't take that chance.
